injustice /ɪnˈdʒʌstɪs/

(injustices) 

1. N-VAR Injustice is a lack of fairness in a situation. 不公正 

例： They'll continue to fight injustice. 他们将继续与不公正的现象抗争。 

2. N-COUNT An injustice is an action or statement in which someone judges you or treats you unfairly. 不公正的行为; 不公平的评论 

例： Calling them a bunch of capricious kids with half-formed ideas does them an injustice. 把他们称作一群懵懂无知、喜怒无常的孩子是冤枉了他们。

</div>

